# GSTACK Workflow (mandatory for every sprint)

**Never use quick Cursor mode without gstack.** Read and execute skills from `.gstack/` (→ `~/gstack`). Do not skip phases or improvise a lighter process.

## Mandatory 3-phase flow (every task)

| # | Skill | Purpose |
|---|-------|---------|
| 1 | `@gstack-plan-eng-review` | Architecture, risks, dependencies, impact/migration/deployment analysis — **lock plan before coding** |
| 2 | `@gstack-careful` | Production-safe implementation: tenant isolation, backwards compatibility, no regressions |
| 3 | `@gstack-review` | Code, security, performance, architecture validation, production validation |

### Supplementary skills (use when applicable)

| Skill | When |
|-------|------|
| `@gstack-investigate` | Bugs/regressions — root cause before fix |
| `@gstack-qa` | Browser QA, mobile-first, zero console errors |
| `@gstack-deploy` / `land-and-deploy` | After implementation — merge + prod rollout |

Chain: **plan → careful implement → review → (qa) → deploy**.

## Architecture guardrails (never break)

- Snapshot system (assistant/agent runtime snapshots)
- WebSocket pipeline (`/admin`, `/widget`, reconnect)
- Auth + refresh (httpOnly cookies, JWT)
- RAG pipeline (retrieval, citations, chunking)
- Tool isolation + tenant boundaries
- Deploy pipeline (`infra/scripts/deploy-production.sh`)
- Production nginx — **only** `agent.neeklo.ru`; never touch other vhosts/upstreams/certs

## Implementation rules

- Analyze first — read code, trace data flow, check git before changing
- Minimal invasive diffs; no full architecture rewrites
- No mock logic, fake data, or placeholder pages in shipped code
- Strict TypeScript — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Mobile-first UI; RU-first copy
- Production-safe migrations only; backwards compatible

## Required validation (after every sprint)

```bash
pnpm typecheck
pnpm test
pnpm lint
pnpm build
```

Production tasks **also require**:

```bash
./infra/scripts/deploy-production.sh
```

Then verify: health, widget.js, /widget/, websocket, pm2 status.

## Required report (after every sprint)

Write `docs/M{N}_REPORT.md` including:

- Architecture changes
- Changed files
- Migrations (if any)
- Nginx / PM2 changes (if touched)
- Deploy steps + **rollback notes**
- Production validation (curl, pm2, nginx)
- Unresolved risks
- Readiness %

## Production baseline (agent.neeklo.ru)

**Readiness ~92%** — stable: AI runtime, RAG, widget runtime, native tool calling, Ollama/OpenRouter/OpenAI, realtime, deploy pipeline, snapshots.

**Next sprints:** analytics, team/settings, billing, workflow builder, voice/video, automation runtime, advanced tools, OCR/docx/xlsx ingestion.

## Quality bar

1. Analyze first
2. No mock logic
3. Production-ready only
4. Strict TypeScript
5. Mobile-first
6. Zero console errors
7. Zero TS errors
